==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Substyle
<hw>Sub"style`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Dialing)</fld>
<def>A right line on which the style, or gnomon, of a dial is erected;
being the common section of the face of the dial and a plane
perpendicular to it passing through the style.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>substile</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsulphate</ent>⟦br⟧
